#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
aq-loop â€” Outer orchestration loop for autonomous multi-agent task execution.

Loop-engineering pattern (Scheduleâ†’Triageâ†’Groundâ†’Executeâ†’Verifyâ†’Escalate):

  1. TRIAGE   â€” pop task from backlog or accept --intent
  2. GROUND   â€” load hints + skills; fan-out parallel research probes to local agent
                (Qwen3-35B) and antigravity (Gemini) for grounded context
  3. EXECUTE  â€” run aq-agent-loop (inner ReAct loop with full tool set)
  4. VERIFY   â€” check COMPLETED: marker; fan-out acceptance review to antigravity reviewer;
                re-queue with review findings if reviewer REJECTED
  5. LOOP     â€” if incomplete and iterations remain, rebuild prompt with evidence
  6. ESCALATE â€” after max iterations, write escalation to issues-backlog.md

Fan-out is on by default. Use --no-fanout to disable. Fan-out is best-effort:
delegation failures fall back gracefully to hints-only grounding.

Usage:
  aq-loop --intent "implement X"                  explicit task (fan-out enabled)
  aq-loop --from-backlog                          pop first [OPEN] from issues-backlog.md
  aq-loop --from-backlog --dry-run                show grounded prompt, no execution
  aq-loop --intent "task" --max-iter 5            override max iterations (default 3)
  aq-loop --intent "task" --no-fanout             skip parallel probes (local only)
  aq-loop --intent "task" --fanout-timeout 60     shorter probe wait (default 120s)
  aq-loop --check                                 print current LOOP_STATE.json
  aq-loop --list-open                             list [OPEN] items from issues-backlog.md
"""

