4. EXECUTE  â€” use edit_file over write_file. One targeted change per slice.
5. VERIFY   â€” run validate_before_commit; fix any failure; re-run tier0 gate.
6. DOC-UPDATE â€” mark [OPEN] â†’ [DONE] in issues-backlog.md if applicable.
7. COMMIT   â€” git_add + git_commit (type(scope): description); then store_memory.

COMPLETION SIGNAL (mandatory):
After store_memory succeeds your FINAL output MUST start with exactly:
